Thrilled Japanese fans welcomed Hideki Matsuyama’s historic Masters victory on Monday, with broadcasters close to tears and the country’s prime minister hailing the win as a bright spot during the pandemic. “Matsuyama Masters” trended on Twitter after the 29-year-old earned himself a place in history by becoming the first Japanese man to capture a major golf title. “Matsuyama opens the door of history,” declared the Asahi Shimbun newspaper. In Japan, the one-stroke victory came early on Monday morning, with some broadcasters carrying live footage of his final round 73 that saw him finish on 10-under par.